<div id="review_1689159982" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1689159982" />
    <a title="Patty" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4833749-patty"><img alt="Patty" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1689159982?book_show_action=true">Jul 05, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Patty" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Patty" href="/user/show/4833749-patty">Patty</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1689159982" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15551353464715860032">Living in a mouldering home in sweltering Torturpuram, on the Bay of Bengal, middle-aged Sripathi writes ad copy by day and deals with his overbearing mother, loving but hectoring wife and rebellious son at home. Estranged from his beloved daughter who rejected a traditional life to move to Vancouver and marry a Westerner Sripathi&apos;s life is upended by a phone call bringing tragic news that requires him to travel to Canada and bring his granddaughter back to India. Anita Rau Badami vividly descri</span>
  <span id="freeText15551353464715860032" style="display:none">Living in a mouldering home in sweltering Torturpuram, on the Bay of Bengal, middle-aged Sripathi writes ad copy by day and deals with his overbearing mother, loving but hectoring wife and rebellious son at home. Estranged from his beloved daughter who rejected a traditional life to move to Vancouver and marry a Westerner Sripathi's life is upended by a phone call bringing tragic news that requires him to travel to Canada and bring his granddaughter back to India. Anita Rau Badami vividly describes the political, physical and social climates of Torturpuram and the struggles of the older generation to adapt to their changing world. Her dialogue begs to be read aloud, so expertly does she capture the cadence of her characters' conversation—especially the bantering between Sripathi and his wife. It's a book about family and how love can curdle and rot relationships but also heal and redeem.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15551353464715860032" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


